---
title: Spinach and Turkey Meatloaves with Mashed Potatoes and Green Beans
description: Veggie alert! This recipe features not one but two wholesome ingredients from the produce section: spinach and green beans. The spinach is tucked into ground turkey meatloaves with mozzarella, acting as the hearty backbone of the mix. Meanwhile, the green beans sit pretty on the plate, providing a crisp and satisfying contrast to the creamy mashed potatoes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/spinach-and-turkey-meatloaves-334f053e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/spinach-and-turkey-meatloaves-89ae9b01.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 460 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spinach-and-turkey-meatloaves-5942a2614f78db7dda15d082
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch cubes and place in a large #pot{} with a big pinch of @salt{} and enough @water{} to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a knife, about ~{12%minutes} total (we'll be adding more items to the pot after 7 minutes).

Thinly slice @Garlic{4%clove}. Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}. Add @Spinach{10%ounce} and toss until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove spinach from pan and place on a #cutting board{}. Finely chop, then transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Add @White Bread{2%slice} and @Milk{2%tablespoon} (we sent more) to bowl with spinach. Squish everything with your hands until bread turns pasty. Add @Mozzarella Cheese{1%cup}, @Ground Turkey{20%ounce}, @Meatloaf Spice Blend{2%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{} (we used 1 tsp kosher salt). Thoroughly combine with your hands and shape into four 1-inch-thick meatloaves.

Place meatloaves on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Bake in oven until no longer pink in center, about ~{15%minutes}. About 5 minutes before potatoes are done, add @Green Beans{12%ounce} to pot. Cook until tender but still crisp, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove green beans with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Drain potatoes once done, then return to pot.

Once meatloaves are done, heat broiler to high. Broil meatloaves until browned on top, about ~{4%minutes}. Meanwhile, return pot with potatoes to stove over low heat. Add @Butter{4%tablespoon} and @Milk{½%cup} (you'll have some milk left over). Mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Add more milk, if needed, to create a creamy consistency.

Divide potatoes, green beans, and meatloaves between plates and serve.